The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem involving set systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem also has connections to graph theory and expansion, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) categories. The use of probabilistic techniques and the focus on random models could suggest a connection to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
